Brian Klawiter posted a message on his company's Facebook page on Tuesday in which he said openly gay people are not welcome at his business in Grandville, Michigan . 
  He said he would not hesitate to refuse service to an openly gay person because he considers homosexuality to be wrong . 
  Critics have accused him of trying to cash in on the anti-gay backlash that cost an Indiana pizzeria over $840,000  . 
  He claims he was taking a stand for conservative Christian values and that people with guns would get a discount . 
 